</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D0836D113075C59FF15FB5CCFF2FAAE" blockId="3.[174,1233,1057,1307]" pageId="3" pageNumber="456">
Bionomics. Ukrainian collected material dates from 24 April to 14 June. It develops internally in stems 
<taxonomicName id="AAB74D5213075C59FE7CFB7CCF35FB4E" box="[394,544,1249,1275]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Urtica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="456" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dioica">
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC313075C59FE7CFB7CCF35FB4E" box="[394,544,1249,1275]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="456">Urtica dioica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in one generation per year. This species is common in most of 
<collectingCountry id="15A0764113075C59FF3AFA9CCC39FAAE" box="[204,300,1281,1307]" name="Ukraine" pageId="3" pageNumber="456">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
but only in spring and early summer.
</paragraph>
